            <li><strong>Immediate requirements:</strong> Register with Hello Work for employment insurance, health insurance/pension enrollment, My Number collection, and income tax withholding setup : all within 10 days of first hire.</li>
            <li><strong>Payroll complexity:</strong> Japanese payroll includes base salary, allowances, social insurance (15% employee + 15% employer), income tax withholding, and resident tax collection starting year two.</li>
            <li><strong>HR  tools:</strong> freee HR (¥3-5K/mo), Money Forward HR (¥2.8K+/mo), and SmartHR (¥600/user/mo) handle most SME needs. Add KING OF TIME (¥300/user/mo) for attendance tracking.</li>
            <li><strong>Labor law protection:</strong> Japan strongly protects employees. Firing requires objective rational grounds. Fixed-term contracts that renew repeatedly create indefinite employment rights.</li>
            <li><strong>Paid leave compliance:</strong> All employees earn paid leave after 6 months. Since 2019, employers must ensure employees take at least 5 days annually : penalties apply for non-compliance.</li>
          </ul>
        </aside>

        <div class="guide-disclaimer">
          <p><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Japanese labor law is complex and regularly updated. This guide covers general SME requirements. Consult a 社会保険労務士 (sharo-shi / SR consultant) for specific compliance advice.</p>
        </div>

